$interpreted: Roger: Outta my way! Outta my way!
Roger: Kittyeyes, are you alright?

Kittyeyes: I'm fine...
Look out, behind you!
Roger: You're one stubborn fella, ain't you!
General: It appears that you care a lot about the girl behind you. Once we capture her, you will have no choice but to surrender.
Roger: I dare you!

General: You don't have another hand to protect her now. 
Blame yourself for your own incompetence!
Kittyeyes: Brother Roger, you...
Kittyeyes: Bro Roger, NO!
Kittyeyes: Brother Roger, didn't you promise that we will live a happy life together? Please, return to your previous kind and gentle self!
Roger: ......
Roger: I, I'm back...

Kittyeyes: Thank goodness, we don't have to be separated from each other again... 
Like you promised, we will always be together,
Kittyeyes: happily ever after...
Roger: ... What are you talking about? We siblings have always been together, haven't we? Not only did we survive Atlas together,
Roger: we grew up in Elana Village too...

Kittyeyes: The Elana Village?
No, that's your younger sister Lina...

Roger: Lina!? Who's Lina?
My blood-related sister has always been you, Kittyeyes, and only you, right?
Kittyeyes: .....
Roger: ... Kittyeyes, I'm feeling a bit exhausted. Let me get some shut-eye, ok?

Kittyeyes: Uh-huh, sure. 
Take your time and rest well.
Kittyeyes: I'll take care of everything...

Kittyeyes: He's safe, nothing more I can ask for. 
Anything else is minor compared to that...
Kittyeyes: Brother, there's an abandoned shack behind that forest. Not only is it concealed and safe, there's also a nearby village to trade for food.
Kittyeyes: It fits us perfectly!
Roger: I expect no less from my trustworthy little sister. You never fail me.

Roger: Hope we can live a peaceful life from now on. 
If I can see you find a good husband, I will have no regrets in life.
Kittyeyes: Now's not the time to talk about that. We should get moving quickly.
Kittyeyes: Brother, is something wrong?

Roger: Kittyeyes, 
did I... forget something important...

Kittyeyes: You will eventually remember it someday.
We should not think about that now, or else your head's gonna start hurting again.

Roger: Hmm, you have a point...
Let's go.
